# Assumptions

The system assumes that users provide correct soil values and that the trained dataset accurately represents real agricultural conditions.

---

# Limitations

- Prediction quality depends on the training dataset.
- Incorrect input values may reduce accuracy.
- Weather changes beyond historical data cannot always be predicted.

---

# Summary

The Requirement Analysis phase transforms agricultural challenges into software requirements. By clearly defining user needs, system capabilities, and technical requirements, this phase provides the foundation for building an intelligent, reliable, and scalable crop recommendation platform.